Q10) In your ogranization for abstraction of continuity and ease-of-use for managing hard drive replacement, repartitioning and backup you need to create a new logical volume "datastore" inside volume group "database" with the following keynotes - The logical volume should be of 50 extends, Volume group physical extent size must be 16 MB, It should be mounted under /common/classes with ext4 on your machine and it should automount after reboot as well.
Q11) Your System needs more memory resources and the RAM is full so you need to create a new SWAP partition of 200M and make it active on boot time on your machine.
Q12) You are a Linux/Unix System Administrator and you need to create a compressed gzip archive file for your company "/my_backup.tar.gz" and that file should have data as located on /usr/local on your machine.
Q13) To provide inline data reduction for Linux in the form of deduplication, compression, and thin provisioning in your company you need to set up a VDO volume named "vgrp" using all available empty disks, Give xfs file system to the mapper /dev/mapper/vgrp and mount it on /datadisk on your machine and it should be available after reboot as well.
Q14) You are System Adminstrator working for a project in your Organization and you need to configure the permissions so copy the file /etc/fstab to /var/tmp, the file /var/tmp/fstab should be owned by the root user, belongs to the group root and should not be executable by anyone, the user Michael is able to read and write /var/tmp/fstab, the user John can neither write nor read /var/tmp/fstab and all others users (current or future) have the ability to read /var/tmp/fstab on your machine.
